channel.title: objectX = ? && ovjectY = ? // i need help wtf is this? lol
channel.description:
ok, basically all i wanna know is.
what is "objectX'? what is "objectY"? How do i know the objectX and objectY of a object??
(I"m adding/deleting objects, please help me with ^^^)
Thanks!

item.title: objectX = ? && ovjectY = ? // i need help wtf is this? lol
item.dc:creator: @raulhenriq raulhenriq
item.description:
@raulhenriq wrote:

L30tegna:

that are coords look at you emotions tabs on the top you see run and there you see the coord x and y[br][br][size=1]Posted on: February 26, 2008, 01:05:43 AM[/size][hr][br][br][size=1]Posted on: February 26, 2008, 01:06:41 AM[/size][hr]you sEE?

At most servers that doesnt appear.
X and Y is the coordinates, that you use for add some objects,npcs or teleports.
To get the X or Y coordinates you must have the command ::mypos or something.
Else if you dont get it, go to mopar client and at game press f4.

U need to replace the objectX with the first number u got, and the objectY with the second.

To add objects, search for and object id that you sure have been added before and search at client.
Then you will see something like “make global object” there you can make new objects.
To add npcs open autospawn.cfg and get a npc id and coordinates.
Hope i helped.
